description:
Ministry of Health and Welfare of South Korea informs that self - isolation exemption is possible for travelers, who have vaccinated in Korea, and are entering overseas. Additional requirements beside vaccination  in Korea before departure, traveler should provide negative test result for COVID - 19 and have no clinical symptoms of COVID - 19;
As of the date of entry, traveler must not have entered from countries like South Africa or Brazil, where the mutant virus is endemic
The policy is to be effective on entries from May 5, 2021
